00:10:04,125 --> 00:10:05,833
[HANA]
You liar! I don't believe it!

256
00:10:05,916 --> 00:10:08,125
Too bad. It's true.

257
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:10,458
[HANA] Fine, but you
have to do it, as well.

258
00:10:10,541 --> 00:10:11,625
Huh?

259
00:10:11,708 --> 00:10:12,708
Do what now?

260
00:10:12,791 --> 00:10:14,291
I want you to pee
for me right now!

261
00:10:14,375 --> 00:10:16,250
I'll watch, so whip it out!

262
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:17,708
Do that and I'll believe you.

263
00:10:17,791 --> 00:10:19,541
No, I couldn't "do that"!
It's way weird!

264
00:10:19,625 --> 00:10:22,250
You saw me "do that," so I've
gotta watch you "do that"!

265
00:10:22,333 --> 00:10:23,791
Otherwise, we can't
make things even!

266
00:10:23,875 --> 00:10:25,375
Now, bust it out,
and take a whiz.

267
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:27,583
Or refuse, then I'll kill
you and off myself.

268
00:10:27,666 --> 00:10:29,083
[KIYOSHI]
All right! Fine!

269
00:10:30,083 --> 00:10:31,708
Are you sure...
you wanna see this?

270
00:10:31,791 --> 00:10:33,375
[HANA]
Of course I do.

271
00:10:33,458 --> 00:10:35,625
[KIYOSHI grunts]

272
00:10:35,708 --> 00:10:36,500
[HANA]
What are you doing?

273
00:10:36,583 --> 00:10:37,875
[KIYOSHI]
Uh...

274
00:10:37,958 --> 00:10:39,666
You saw me up front,
so turn around.

275
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:40,958
[gasps]

276
00:10:44,625 --> 00:10:46,791
Whoa! Isn't that kinda close?

277
00:10:46,875 --> 00:10:48,875
[HANA] You were even
closer when I was going.

278
00:10:48,958 --> 00:10:50,708
Now hurry up and get started.

279
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:55,708
'Kay...

280
00:11:00,041 --> 00:11:01,250
--[GAKUTO] Sir Kiyoshi!
--[BOTH gasp]

281
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:02,166
Where art thou?

282
00:11:02,250 --> 00:11:03,833
[KIYOSHI]
Gakuto, what's up?

283
00:11:03,916 --> 00:11:06,625
You forgot to dispose of some
piles of debris yet again.

284
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:07,416
Tch.

285
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,250
Oh, sorry.

286
00:11:09,333 --> 00:11:10,291
Once that's been dealt with,

287
00:11:10,375 --> 00:11:12,041
you're to return
to work immediately.

288
00:11:12,125 --> 00:11:13,625
Right!

289
00:11:13,708 --> 00:11:15,625
You saved my ass, Gakuto.

290
00:11:15,708 --> 00:11:17,291
Much appreciated.

291
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:21,750
[KIYOSHI] The question is,
did he mean to save me just now?

292
00:11:21,833 --> 00:11:23,541
I dunno what angle he's working.

293
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:27,458
Maybe he'll try to get special
treatment for squealing on me.

294
00:11:27,541 --> 00:11:30,541
Oh shit! He's heading straight
for the hole I'm digging.

295
00:11:30,625 --> 00:11:34,583
This is bad! Damn! If he finds
it, he'll have definitive proof!

296
00:11:34,666 --> 00:11:36,000
I've come too far...

297
00:11:36,083 --> 00:11:37,708
Only one thing left to do.

298
00:11:37,791 --> 00:11:39,500
Stay your hand.

299
00:11:39,583 --> 00:11:40,791
Very smart.

300
00:11:40,875 --> 00:11:42,666
Coming here where
you're unaccompanied

301
00:11:42,750 --> 00:11:43,875
to dig your way out.

302
00:11:43,958 --> 00:11:45,041
[KIYOSHI gulps]

303
00:11:46,083 --> 00:11:47,666
[GAKUTO]
I want you to break out.

304
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:48,833
[KIYOSHI]
Hm?

305
00:11:48,916 --> 00:11:50,208
And yours truly shall
provide assistance

306
00:11:50,291 --> 00:11:51,708
in your daring escape.

307
00:11:51,791 --> 00:11:52,916
[KIYOSHI] Hold on now.

308
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,541
You want to help me break out?

309
00:11:54,625 --> 00:11:56,250
That's right.

310
00:11:56,333 --> 00:11:58,708
[KIYOSHI] So what's the deal
with all the creepy sumo threats

311
00:11:58,791 --> 00:12:00,291
you've been dishing out?

312
00:12:00,375 --> 00:12:02,708
Clever signals that I would help
you abscond from this hellhole.

313
00:12:02,791 --> 00:12:04,125
How was I supposed
to know that?!

314
00:12:04,208 --> 00:12:06,375
And why do you want
to help me anyway?!

315
00:12:06,458 --> 00:12:08,791
The upcoming student
sumo tournament--

316
00:12:08,875 --> 00:12:12,041
That day is also a momentous
one for yours truly.

317
00:12:13,291 --> 00:12:15,333
Specifics forthcoming.

318
00:12:20,916 --> 00:12:22,250
[MEIKO]
Madam President...

319
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:23,750
May I wash your back for you?

320
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:24,833
Thank you.

321
00:12:24,916 --> 00:12:27,083
You may proceed,
Madam Vice President.

322
00:12:27,166 --> 00:12:28,375
[MEIKO]
Incidentally,

323
00:12:28,458 --> 00:12:29,750
I've heard that the
top-ranked sumo wrestlers

324
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:32,208
have assistants who help
them wash their backs...

325
00:12:32,291 --> 00:12:33,916
...as well as their derrieres.

326
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,750
What're you saying?!

327
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:39,458
You look at me and think about
sumo wrestlers? Am I fat?

328
00:12:39,541 --> 00:12:41,666
No! It was just an
interesting factoid.

329
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:43,125
I meant nothing by it!

330
00:12:43,208 --> 00:12:45,208
[MARI] I apologize for you
having to spend your weekend

331
00:12:45,291 --> 00:12:46,166
overseeing the boys.

332
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:47,875
No, I don't mind that at all.

333
00:12:47,958 --> 00:12:50,208
It's just... Are you
sure it's a good idea

334
00:12:50,291 --> 00:12:52,000
to disobey the
Chairman's orders?

335
00:12:52,083 --> 00:12:53,583
We're not supposed to
make the prisoners work

336
00:12:53,666 --> 00:12:54,708
on their days off.

337
00:12:54,791 --> 00:12:56,125
The Chairman's rule
granting free time

338
00:12:56,208 --> 00:12:58,458
on the weekends applies
to model prisoners only.

339
00:12:58,541 --> 00:13:00,291
And since their work
is behind schedule,

340
00:13:00,375 --> 00:13:02,166
then they are not
model prisoners.

341
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:03,833
[MEIKO]
You couldn't be more right.

342
00:13:03,916 --> 00:13:05,125
This is our duty.

343
00:13:05,208 --> 00:13:06,958
When I think of how
those peeping toms are

344
00:13:07,041 --> 00:13:09,208
going to be released
in half a month,

345
00:13:09,291 --> 00:13:11,583
I can't sit by and do nothing.

346
00:13:14,166 --> 00:13:15,791
It looks like Mari was here,

347
00:13:15,875 --> 00:13:17,458
and she saw what
was on my screen.

348
00:13:17,541 --> 00:13:19,958
Maybe that's why she took
the boys' free time away.

349
00:13:20,041 --> 00:13:21,291
To pay me back.

350
00:13:21,375 --> 00:13:23,458
Oh yes, Cruelty, thy name is...

351
00:13:23,541 --> 00:13:24,625
...Woman!

352
00:13:24,708 --> 00:13:26,083
But just in case,

353
00:13:26,166 --> 00:13:28,583
I'd better take this home
before she finds it... too!

354
00:13:28,666 --> 00:13:32,208
[JOE, ANDRE singing]

355
00:13:32,291 --> 00:13:34,291
[GAKUTO] Yours truly has
a motive less fleeting

356
00:13:34,375 --> 00:13:37,625
than a sumo date with
the fairer sex, my friend.

357
00:13:37,708 --> 00:13:38,958
Art thou at all familiar with

358
00:13:39,041 --> 00:13:40,791
"The Romance of the
Three Kingdoms"?

359
00:13:40,875 --> 00:13:43,416
Well, I've heard the name
before, at the very least.

360
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:45,833
We look back to the
later Han Dynasty,

361
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:48,458
the end of the second
century, Common Era.

362
00:13:48,541 --> 00:13:50,458
The emperor dies,
and the eunuchs

363
00:13:50,541 --> 00:13:52,208
--known as the Ten Attendants--
--Just get to the point!

364
00:13:52,291 --> 00:13:53,041
[GAKUTO]
Very well.

365
00:13:53,125 --> 00:13:54,791
To make a long story short:

366
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:57,000
Quadrennially, the Three
Kingdoms figurine expo

367
00:13:57,083 --> 00:13:59,666
is held in Akihabara the
same day as your sumo match!

368
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:01,083
It's quite simple, really.

369
00:14:01,166 --> 00:14:03,125
Yours truly needs the
limited edition Guan Yu

370
00:14:03,208 --> 00:14:05,583
and Red Hare figurines
to complete my collection!

371
00:14:05,666 --> 00:14:07,500
And you had the nerve to
call my motive fleeting?

372
00:14:07,583 --> 00:14:08,958
[GAKUTO]
Not even the same ballpark!

373
00:14:09,041 --> 00:14:11,083
We're talking once-every-
four-years limited edition!

374
00:14:11,166 --> 00:14:12,333
[KIYOSHI]
All right, I get it.

375
00:14:12,416 --> 00:14:13,916
That's why you want
to break out with me.

376
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:17,041
Sir Kiyoshi, you really are
a buffoon, you know that?

377
00:14:17,125 --> 00:14:17,916
We'd both be caught--

378
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,416
Yo! What're you guys up to?

379
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:20,958
Playing a little gomoku.

380
00:14:21,041 --> 00:14:22,125
You want next?

381
00:14:22,208 --> 00:14:24,583
Man, that's boring.
Count me out, bro.

382
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:27,208
Kiyoshi, it's a one-hour trip
one-way from the prison

383
00:14:27,291 --> 00:14:30,583
to the gymnasium where your
sumo date will take place.

384
00:14:30,666 --> 00:14:32,791
If we assume that watching
the matches takes one hour,

385
00:14:32,875 --> 00:14:35,916
then we're talking a grand total
of three hours with you missing.

386
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,458
But if you go missing for three
hours during work detail,

387
00:14:38,541 --> 00:14:40,416
the overseers will
definitely find out.

388
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:41,750
You got a point.

389
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:43,458
[GAKUTO] Simply put, it is
categorically impossible

390
00:14:43,541 --> 00:14:45,250
for you to successfully
break out on your own,

391
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:47,250
and that's why I said
I'd aid your attempt.

392
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:49,208
Saturday afternoon,
during the three hours

393
00:14:49,291 --> 00:14:50,916
when you'll escape to
go on your sumo date

394
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,708
as well as buy both Three
Kingdoms figures I want.

395
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:56,541
Yours truly will distract
the gaze of the overseers.

396
00:14:56,625 --> 00:14:59,125
But how the hell are you gonna
distract them for that long?

397
00:14:59,208 --> 00:15:01,291
[GAKUTO chuckles]
I have a stratagem.

398
00:15:01,375 --> 00:15:02,875
Now pay attention.

399
00:15:02,958 --> 00:15:04,375
[KIYOSHI]
No way!

400
00:15:04,458 --> 00:15:07,083
A map of the school disguised
as a gomoku game! Badass!

401
00:15:16,458 --> 00:15:19,291
Patrolling the campus
by night, are we?

402
00:15:19,375 --> 00:15:21,041
Were you heading home?
Be careful--

403
00:15:21,125 --> 00:15:23,083
--[thud]
--[gasps]

404
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:31,291
[MARI]
Starting tomorrow...

405
00:15:31,375 --> 00:15:35,000
Those boys will learn the true
meaning of cruel and unusual.

406
00:15:35,083 --> 00:15:36,333
Despite their crimes,

407
00:15:36,416 --> 00:15:38,000
I want to ensure that
they don't end up becoming

408
00:15:38,083 --> 00:15:41,583
the deplorable kind
of pervert that you are.

409
00:15:41,666 --> 00:15:42,791
[CHAIRMAN]
Good luck with that.

410
00:15:42,875 --> 00:15:44,041
Hmph.

411
00:15:49,208 --> 00:15:50,250
The hole you're digging is

412
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:52,041
in the back of the
refuse shack, here.

413
00:15:52,125 --> 00:15:53,958
Through which, if you
can extricate yourself,

414
00:15:54,041 --> 00:15:56,708
you'll make your escape
without anyone the wiser.

415
00:15:56,791 --> 00:15:59,208
The question is, how do I
keep our guards distracted

416
00:15:59,291 --> 00:16:01,291
from your absence
for three hours?

417
00:16:01,375 --> 00:16:04,375
The Underground Student Council
is rather observant, after all.

418
00:16:04,458 --> 00:16:06,250
I appreciate the help, dude.

419
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:08,000
But from everything
you're saying,

420
00:16:08,083 --> 00:16:11,208
it doesn't sound like breaking
out is even a possibility.

421
00:16:11,291 --> 00:16:14,208
[GAKUTO chuckles]
Never fear, Brave Knight!

422
00:16:14,291 --> 00:16:15,625
I, myself, have been called

423
00:16:15,708 --> 00:16:17,958
the most resourceful
general in Nerima.

424
00:16:18,041 --> 00:16:19,791
Yours truly has a
beauty of a plan

425
00:16:19,875 --> 00:16:22,333
that will make the
impossible possible.

426
00:16:23,416 --> 00:16:25,458
The cart's full. I'll dump it.

427
00:16:25,541 --> 00:16:27,083
[MEIKO]
Permission granted.

428
00:16:33,833 --> 00:16:35,458
[GAKUTO]
Dammit, Kiyoshi!

429
00:16:35,541 --> 00:16:36,750
What is up?

430
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:38,458
Once again, your
dereliction of duty

431
00:16:38,541 --> 00:16:40,375
has lead to me being
horrifically savaged!

432
00:16:40,458 --> 00:16:42,000
Aw damn, that sucks.

433
00:16:42,083 --> 00:16:43,500
My bad, dude.

434
00:16:43,583 --> 00:16:45,375
[GAKUTO] After everything
I've been through, that's it?

435
00:16:45,458 --> 00:16:47,666
Get on your knees, and plead
for my forgiveness, right now!

436
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:49,000
You need to calm down.

437
00:16:49,083 --> 00:16:50,125
None of it matters.

438
00:16:50,208 --> 00:16:51,541
It matters to me, you oaf!

439
00:16:51,625 --> 00:16:53,958
Now stand ready to accept
a pummeling long overdue!

440
00:16:54,041 --> 00:16:55,333
What's the big idea?

441
00:16:55,416 --> 00:16:56,541
[GAKUTO]
Apologize!

442
00:16:56,625 --> 00:16:57,666
[HANA] What do you jerks
think you're doing?

443
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:58,250
[BOTH gasp]

444
00:16:58,333 --> 00:16:59,125
[HANA grunts]

445
00:16:59,208 --> 00:17:00,250
Hya!

446
00:17:06,291 --> 00:17:07,333
[MEIKO]
Care to explain?

447
00:17:07,416 --> 00:17:08,083
[GAKUTO, KIYOSHI gasp]

448
00:17:08,166 --> 00:17:09,291
It wasn't us!

449
00:17:09,375 --> 00:17:10,791
Hana knocked the shack down!

450
00:17:10,875 --> 00:17:13,041
The two of them were fighting
and crashed into the shed.

451
00:17:13,125 --> 00:17:14,375
[BOTH]
Hey, she's lying!

452
00:17:14,458 --> 00:17:16,791
Heads or tails, boys.
Choose one now.

453
00:17:16,875 --> 00:17:19,666
--[BOTH] Uh...
--[MEIKO] I said choose one!

454
00:17:19,750 --> 00:17:20,958
I choose heads.

455
00:17:21,041 --> 00:17:22,375
Fine, tails.

456
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:24,000
--[GAKUTO yelps]
--[KIYOSHI screams]

457
00:17:24,083 --> 00:17:25,500
[BOTH groaning]

458
00:17:25,583 --> 00:17:27,250
[MEIKO] The president
suggested we increase

459
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:29,291
the intensity of your
discipline regimen.

460
00:17:29,375 --> 00:17:32,250
So I brought along
this riding crop.

461
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:33,666
[GAKUTO gasps]

462
00:17:35,041 --> 00:17:38,375
[muffled screaming]

463
00:17:38,458 --> 00:17:40,666
[GAKUTO]
I can't breathe!

464
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:43,458
[KIYOSHI screams]

465
00:17:43,541 --> 00:17:45,166
Don't squirm!

466
00:17:45,250 --> 00:17:46,458
Don't make a sound!

467
00:17:46,541 --> 00:17:47,708
[MEIKO grunts]

468
00:17:47,791 --> 00:17:50,000
--[whipping continues]
--[KIYOSHI screaming]

469
00:17:50,083 --> 00:17:51,791
They're getting it really bad.

470
00:17:51,875 --> 00:17:53,416
[JOE]
Must suck. [coughs]

471
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:54,291
Yeah...

472
00:17:54,375 --> 00:17:56,041
Remind me not to pick tails.

473
00:17:56,125 --> 00:17:58,125
But given the options,
heads looks all right.

474
00:17:58,208 --> 00:18:01,166
You two are hereby ordered to
rebuild the shed you destroyed.

475
00:18:01,250 --> 00:18:02,708
[BOTH]
No way!

476
00:18:02,791 --> 00:18:04,541
--[GAKUTO] Nigh unthinkable!
--[KIYOSHI] Just the two of us?!

477
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:08,458
[BOTH sob]

478
00:18:08,541 --> 00:18:09,875
[BOTH chuckle]

479
00:18:09,958 --> 00:18:11,250
[GAKUTO]
Well played, sir.

480
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:12,458
Back atcha!

481
00:18:12,541 --> 00:18:13,833
Stage One of the plan complete.

482
00:18:13,916 --> 00:18:15,541
And it couldn't
have gone better!

483
00:18:15,625 --> 00:18:18,083
Cut some notches in the
support posts with the saw,

484
00:18:18,166 --> 00:18:20,625
pretend to start a fight, and
bring the shed crashing down.

485
00:18:20,708 --> 00:18:22,958
The perfect reason to
leave us by the escape hole

486
00:18:23,041 --> 00:18:24,125
for the rest of the day.

487
00:18:24,208 --> 00:18:25,541
Flawless victory.

488
00:18:25,625 --> 00:18:26,666
[HANA]
What are you doing?

489
00:18:26,750 --> 00:18:27,333
[BOTH gasp]

490
00:18:27,416 --> 00:18:28,416
Don't give me that.

491
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:30,375
Now get your asses
in gear, Dickbags.

492
00:18:30,458 --> 00:18:33,000
[KIYOSHI] So, uh... Hana,
are you planning to stay here?

493
00:18:33,083 --> 00:18:34,458
Of course I'm staying.

494
00:18:34,541 --> 00:18:36,083
I have to guard you two idiots.

495
00:18:36,166 --> 00:18:37,666
All right, Brainiac.

496
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:40,208
Now Hana's gonna be guarding us.
You got a Plan B or something?

497
00:18:40,291 --> 00:18:42,250
[chuckles]
Remember, Brave Knight,

498
00:18:42,333 --> 00:18:44,958
you're with the most
resourceful general in Nerima.

499
00:18:45,041 --> 00:18:46,875
[KIYOSHI] So you have something
up your sleeve for this?

500
00:18:46,958 --> 00:18:47,875
[GAKUTO chokes]

501
00:18:47,958 --> 00:18:49,875
I'm afraid to say,

502
00:18:49,958 --> 00:18:52,250
even my strategic mind couldn't
foresee this development.

503
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:53,291
No shit?

504
